type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-0051</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Conversely, assume that every object is merely equipped with both an upshift and a downshift. That a positive object <fr:tex>P</fr:tex> has an upshift <fr:link
href="jms-004X.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-004X">is a proposition</fr:link>, so we can use our assumption that <fr:tex>P</fr:tex> <fr:em>merely</fr:em> has an upshift. That a negative object <fr:tex>N</fr:tex> has a downshift <fr:link
href="jms-004Z.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-004Z">is likewise a proposition</fr:link>, so we can use our assumption that <fr:tex>N</fr:tex> <fr:em>merely</fr:em> has a downshift.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
